<!--
The smallest beet entry: a script that runs on load and prints, the
`node main.js` shape. `<script>` is a raw-text element so the JavaScript body is
verbatim; the `{EvalOnLoad}` verb spread runs it once the entry is built,
binding the process request as `input` and streaming `console.log` to stdout.
-->
<script {EvalOnLoad}>console.log("hello world")</script>
